      "order": 3,
      "alignment": "left",
      "body": "Diagnostic plots to catch problematic samples before drawing biological conclusions. The **coverage-vs-variants scatter** flags low-coverage samples with inflated / deflated variant counts (usually partial drop-out or contamination). The **substitutions-vs-deletions** plot surfaces clade-specific deletion patterns or assembly artefacts. The bar at the bottom shows the per-sample % >= 10x with the 80% reliability cut-off.",
      "wf_tag": "nextflow/viralrecon"
    },
